<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-07-0365 </DOCNO><TEXT>A description is given of energy efficient techniques which have beenincorporated in four grain whisky distilleries for the production ofanimal feed from effluent. The techniques used in the evaporation anddrying stages include mechanical vapour recompression and increasingthe drier efficiency by gas recycle; the use of a gas turbine as partof a CHP scheme is an additional energy efficiency feature. The paybackperiod is around 4 years.</TEXT></DOC>